{"annotations": [{"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "DNA bases", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.6591678857803345, "span": {"begin": 94, "end": 103}}, {"id": ["mesh:D001564"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "benzo(a)pyrene", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.999677300453186, "span": {"begin": 340, "end": 354}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:29865"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "B(a)P", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9994676113128662, "span": {"begin": 356, "end": 361}}, {"id": ["mesh:C482278"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "anti-benzo(a)pyrene diol epoxide", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.999571681022644, "span": {"begin": 381, "end": 413}}, {"id": ["mesh:D015123"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "BPDE", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9895989894866943, "span": {"begin": 415, "end": 419}}, {"id": ["mesh:C418058", "mesh:C040060"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "(+/-)-trans-anti-BPDE-N-2-dG", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9996039271354675, "span": {"begin": 429, "end": 457}}, {"id": ["mesh:C018834"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "aristicholic acid", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9987812042236328, "span": {"begin": 762, "end": 779}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "DNA", "obj": "RNA", "prob": 0.37702327966690063, "span": {"begin": 809, "end": 812}}, {"id": ["mesh:C077580"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "7-(deoxyadenosin-N6-yl) aristolactamI", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9994512796401978, "span": {"begin": 820, "end": 857}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:50323"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "dA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9999699592590332, "span": {"begin": 859, "end": 861}}, {"id": ["mesh:D016604"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "aflatoxin B1", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9998181462287903, "span": {"begin": 962, "end": 974}}, {"id": ["mesh:C028319"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "8,9-dihydro-8- (N7-guanyl)-9-hydroxyaflatoxin B1", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9997894167900085, "span": {"begin": 993, "end": 1041}}, {"id": ["mesh:C514713"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "AFB1-N7-Gua", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9452645778656006, "span": {"begin": 1043, "end": 1054}}, {"id": ["mesh:D016604"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "AFB1", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9958075284957886, "span": {"begin": 1087, "end": 1091}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:35877"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "formamidopyrimidine", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9967799186706543, "span": {"begin": 1092, "end": 1111}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:57258"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "FAPY", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9993536472320557, "span": {"begin": 1113, "end": 1117}}], "text": "Bulky DNA adducts occur when aromatic compounds are metabolically activated and interact with DNA bases. Not all of these bulky adductsare stable, however some&nbsp;have been found to persist and cause mutations during repair or replication. The specific mutation that occurs variesby bulky DNA adduct and by chemical. Exposure to&nbsp;the benzo(a)pyrene (B(a)P) or its metabolite anti-benzo(a)pyrene diol epoxide (BPDE)leads to (+/-)-trans-anti-BPDE-N-2-dG adducts, these adducts are associated with&nbsp;G&rarr;T transversions (Chiapperino et al. 2002; Zhang et al.2000, 2002), the occurrence of these transversions has been observed both in smokers (Anna et al. 2009; Hainaut and Pfeifer 2001)&nbsp;and in non-smokers&nbsp;(DeMarini et al. 2001). Exposure to aristicholic acid (AA) leads to the persistent DNA adduct 7-(deoxyadenosin-N6-yl) aristolactamI (dA&ndash;AAI) adducts and leads to AT&rarr;TA transversions (Arlt&nbsp;et al.,&nbsp;2002). Exposure to aflatoxin B1 has been leads to 8,9-dihydro-8- (N7-guanyl)-9-hydroxyaflatoxin B1 (AFB1-N7-Gua) adducts, which can lead to the AFB1-formamidopyrimidine (FAPY) adduct and ultimately causeG&rarr;T transversions (Bailey et al. 1996; Smela et al. 2002).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:34:59 +0000 2026"}